issue.title: feat: add census choropleth layer
issue.body:
## Summary
- overlay US Census statistics on OKC map as a choropleth
- allow choosing population or median income by county
- add topojson and us-atlas dependencies for boundary data
- add @types/topojson-client and rename map import to fix build errors
- restrict choropleth to Oklahoma County and display tract-level statistics
- correctly join ACS results to tract GEOIDs so fill colors render

## Testing
- `npm run lint`
- `npm run build`
- `npm test` *(fails: Missing script: "test")*

performed_via_github_app.name: Codecov
performed_via_github_app.description:
Codecov provides highly integrated tools to group, merge, archive and compare coverage reports. Whether your team is comparing changes in a pull request or reviewing a single commit, Codecov will improve the code review workflow and quality.

## Code coverage done right.¬Æ

1. Upload coverage reports from your CI builds.
2. Codecov merges all builds and languages into one beautiful coherent report.
3. Get commit statuses, pull request comments and coverage overlay via our browser extension.

When Codecov merges your uploads it keeps track of the CI provider (inc. build details) and user specified context, e.g. `#unittest` ~ `#smoketest` or `#oldcode` ~ `#newcode`. You can track the `#unittest` coverage independently of other groups. [Learn more here](
http://docs.codecov.io/docs/flags)

Through **Codecov's Browser Extension** reports overlay directly in GitHub UI to assist in code review in [Chrome](https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/codecov/gedikamndpbemklijjkncpnolildpbgo) or Firefox (https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/codecov/)

*Highly detailed* **pull request comments** and *customizable* **commit statuses** will improve your team's workflow and code coverage incrementally.

**File backed configuration** all through the `codecov.yml`. 

## FAQ
- Do you **merge multiple uploads** to the same commit? **Yes**
- Do you **support multiple languages** in the same project? **Yes**
- Can you **group coverage reports** by project and/or test type? **Yes**
- How does **pricing** work? Only paid users can view reports and post statuses/comments.

commits.message:
Avoid deleting and creating timer needlessly

Previously we cancelled the timer and initialized it again at each
call of move-selection, now we create a timer that cancel itself and
check at each call if the timer is alive before creating a new one.

As a result, for example when keeping C-n pressed and passing e.g. 10
candidates, previously 10 timers were cancelled and created, now only
one timer is created.

pull_request.title: [WIP] Architecture: Separate marketing site from authenticated application
pull_request.body:
Thanks for assigning this issue to me. I'm starting to work on it and will keep this PR's description up to date as I form a plan and make progress.

Original issue description:

> ## Problem
> Currently, the homepage (`/app/src/app/page.tsx`) serves as both marketing landing page AND authenticated dashboard. This creates poor UX where authenticated users see marketing content instead of their dashboard.
> 
> ## Current Issues
> - No authentication-based routing separation
> - Marketing content mixed with app functionality  
> - Confusing user experience for authenticated users
> - No clear entry point differentiation
> - SEO issues with mixed content purpose
> 
> ## Proposed Solution
> 
> ### 1. Create Separate Route Structure
> ```
> Marketing Site:
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ / (homepage - unauthenticated)
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /about  
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /pricing
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /contact
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /auth/login
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /auth/signup
> ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ /auth/forgot-password
> 
> Authenticated App:
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /dashboard (main authenticated entry)
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /clubs/[id]
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /meetings/[id] 
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /profile
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /settings
> ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ /learning/[course]
> ```
> 
> ### 2. Implement Route Protection
> **Create Middleware**: `/app/src/middleware.ts`
> ```typescript
> export function middleware(request: NextRequest) {
>   const { pathname } = request.nextUrl;
>   const token = request.cookies.get('auth_token');
>   
>   // Redirect authenticated users from marketing to dashboard
>   if (token && isMarketingPage(pathname)) {
>     return NextResponse.redirect('/dashboard');
>   }
>   
>   // Redirect unauthenticated users from app to login
>   if (\!token && isAppPage(pathname)) {
>     return NextResponse.redirect('/auth/login');
>   }
> }
> ```
> 
> ### 3. Create Dedicated Layouts
> **Marketing Layout**: `app/(marketing)/layout.tsx`
> - Marketing-focused navigation
> - Call-to-action buttons
> - SEO optimizations
> - No authenticated user state
> 
> **App Layout**: `app/(app)/layout.tsx` 
> - Application navigation
> - User profile dropdown
> - Notification center
> - Club/meeting context
> 
> ### 4. Update Components
> **Navigation Component Separation**:
> - `MarketingNavigation.tsx` - For unauthenticated users
> - `AppNavigation.tsx` - For authenticated users  
> - Context-aware component switching
> 
> ## Technical Requirements
> - [ ] Create `/dashboard` route as main authenticated entry point
> - [ ] Move current homepage features to `/dashboard`
> - [ ] Design new marketing homepage at `/`
> - [ ] Add route protection middleware
> - [ ] Implement authentication-based redirects
> - [ ] Create separate layout components
> - [ ] Update navigation components for context switching
> - [ ] Add loading states for auth checks
> - [ ] Implement proper error boundaries
> 
> ## Files to Create/Modify
> ```
> New Files:
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app/(marketing)/
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ page.tsx (new marketing homepage)
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ about/page.tsx
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pricing/page.tsx
> ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ contact/page.tsx
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app/(app)/
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layout.tsx
> ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dashboard/page.tsx (moved from current homepage)
> ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ [existing app routes]
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/components/MarketingNavigation.tsx
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/components/AppNavigation.tsx
> ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ middleware.ts
> 
> Modified Files:
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app/page.tsx (convert to marketing homepage)
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/components/Navigation.tsx (add context awareness)
> ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx (handle routing logic)
> ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ app/layout.tsx (conditional layouts)
> ```
> 
> ## SEO Considerations
> - Separate meta tags for marketing vs app pages
> - Marketing pages optimized for search engines
> - App pages excluded from search indexing
> - Proper canonical URLs for marketing content
> 
> ## User Experience Flow
> 1. **Unauthenticated User**: Lands on marketing site ‚Üí Signs up ‚Üí Redirected to dashboard
> 2. **Authenticated User**: Direct access to `/` ‚Üí Auto-redirected to `/dashboard`  
> 3. **Logout**: Redirect from app pages to marketing homepage
> 
> ## Priority
> **P0 - Critical for Production UX**
> 
> Labels: `architecture`, `authentication`, `routing`, `UX`, `P0`

issue.title: macOS Keychain: SSH Authentication Failure for Pro Plan Users
issue.body:
**Bug Description**
Subject: SSH Authentication Failure After macOS Keychain Integration - Critical Issue for Pro Plan Users

Description:
I am experiencing a critical authentication issue with Claude Code that has severely impacted my workflow. This problem started approximately 2-3 days ago and appears to be related to the recent change that moved API key storage to macOS Keychain.

Issue Details:
- For the past month, Claude Code worked perfectly via SSH connections
- Since ~2-3 days ago, SSH authentication completely fails with "Missing API key ¬∑ Run /login" 
- Physical machine access still works normally
- I am a Claude.ai Pro Plan subscriber (not API account user)
- The issue occurs specifically when accessing Claude Code through SSH clients like Terminus

Timeline:
- Previous month: SSH access worked flawlessly
- Recent days: Complete SSH authentication failure
- Physical machine: Still functional

Technical Analysis:
Based on the changelog, Claude Code now stores "(Mac-only) API keys in macOS Keychain". This change appears to have broken SSH access because:
1. SSH sessions cannot access the macOS Keychain that requires GUI session context
2. OAuth authentication completes successfully in browser but tokens are not accessible to SSH sessions
3. Physical machine works because it has full GUI session access to Keychain

Steps to Reproduce:
1. SSH into macOS host with Claude Code installed
2. Run `claude` command
3. Execute `/login`
4. Complete OAuth authentication in browser (shows "Login successful")
5. Claude Code still displays "Missing API key ¬∑ Run /login"
6. `/status` shows "Auth Token: [REDACTED] despite successful login

Impact:
This is a critical regression that has completely broken my development workflow. As a Pro Plan subscriber, I cannot use the environment variables workaround since that requires API account access. I believe many SSH users are experiencing this same issue.

Environment:
- macOS host system
- Claude Code version: [current version]
- Installation: npm global
- Account: Claude.ai Pro Plan subscription
- Access method: SSH (Terminus, etc.)

Request:
This issue severely impacts user experience and appears to affect many SSH users. Please:
1. Provide immediate acknowledgment of this regression
2. Prioritize a fix for SSH authentication with macOS Keychain
3. Consider reverting the Keychain-only approach or providing SSH-compatible alternatives
4. Send email updates on progress and resolution

I rely heavily on Claude Code for my development work and this regression has made the tool completely unusable in my primary workflow. Please treat this as a high-priority issue and provide email feedback on the resolution timeline.

Thank you for your urgent attention to this matter.

**Environment Info**

pull_request.title: [WIP] Enhancements for Custom Domain Handling
pull_request.body:
Thanks for asking me to work on this. I will get started on it and keep this PR's description up to date as I form a plan and make progress.

Original description:

> Implement the following improvements for the handling of custom domains in the AdLinkPro repository:
> 
> ### Scalability
> 1. Allow advertisers to use multiple domains, configurable via environment variables.
> 2. Introduce batch updates for tracking links to improve performance when updating large numbers of offers.
> 
> ### Error Handling
> 1. Add detailed error messages for DNS verification failures, such as DNS record not found, timeout, or DNS server unavailable.
> 
> ### SSL Integration
> 1. Enhance SSL certificate issuance by integrating with advanced providers like Cloudflare or AWS ACM for reliability.
> 
> ### DNS Validation
> 1. Add an automatic DNS validation feature when entering a custom domain in the interface.
> 
> ### Enhanced UX
> 1. Improve the advertiser interface by introducing progress indicators for long operations like domain verification and SSL issuance.
> 2. Display domain-specific error messages directly in the list of existing domains.
> 
> ### Testing and Documentation
> 1. Write unit tests for CustomDomainService methods.
> 2. Provide detailed documentation for each method and interface, including usage examples.
> 
> ### Caching
> 1. Implement caching for DNS queries to optimize repeated domain verifications.
> 
> ### Code Optimization
> 1. Refactor methods such as updateTrackingLinksWithDomain to use efficient batch operations.
> 
> Please make these changes while ensuring backward compatibility.

comment.body: @paustian Hello - No, we're not currently developing actively. The specific issue leading to the closure of the plugin is a CSRF vulnerability, which is a relatively straightforward fix. But the plugin will also have to pass the more general tests included in https://wordpress.org/plugins/plugin-check/, which it's not likely to be able to do without some work on the internal libraries. If you'd like to work on it, I'd be happy to consult, to review PRs, or to handle release and communication with wordpress.org, if you would like to help get it up and running.
